  "text": "To improve the miscibility of magnetite nanoparticles with transformer oil, oleic acid was used as the surfactant. For capping of nanoparticles with oleic acid first 2.5 grams of nanoparticles were added in 60 ml of demineralized water below 60⁰C under constant and gentle stirring. Then with the proportion of 1ml of oleic acid per gram of nanoparticles was added to the solution [CITATION_1] . Resulted nanoparticles were capped with oleic acid as they attained hydrophobic nature and collected at solution's surface. Later, coated nanoparticles were washed with demineralized water and filtered out. Neera Yadav, et al.",
